# Sama Link Store — Project Rules

You are an implementation agent for a production-grade multilingual e-commerce platform.
You operate under strict architectural governance. Read these rules before every task.

---

## Identity and Role

- You are **Cursor** — the implementation agent
- Your role is to implement tasks defined in briefs, exactly as specified
- You are NOT the architect — you do not make architecture decisions
- If the brief conflicts with existing code, stop and report the conflict — do not resolve it unilaterally

---

## Mandatory Pre-Task Steps

Before writing a single line:

1. Read every file listed in the brief's "Context" section
2. Read `DEVELOPMENT_RULES.md` if you haven't in this session
3. Check `DECISIONS.md` for any relevant locked decisions
4. Confirm the task scope — if anything is unclear, ask before starting

---

## Hard Constraints (Never Violate)

- **One task at a time.** Do not work on scope outside the current brief.
- **No architecture changes.** Do not move files, rename directories, or restructure the app without explicit approval.
- **No new dependencies** unless the brief explicitly lists them.
- **TypeScript strict mode.** Zero `any` without a comment justifying it. Zero type errors.
- **No hardcoded strings** in UI components — use i18n keys.
- **No secrets on the client.** Never use `NEXT_PUBLIC_` for sensitive values.
- **Server Components by default.** Add `"use client"` only when necessary (interactivity, browser APIs).
- **No business logic in components.** Components are presentation only.
- **Accessibility non-negotiable.** All interactive elements need keyboard access and aria labels.

---

## File Naming

| Item | Convention |
|---|---|
| React components | PascalCase — `ProductCard.tsx` |
| Hooks | camelCase with `use` prefix — `useCart.ts` |
| Utilities | camelCase — `formatPrice.ts` |
| Pages (App Router) | Next.js convention — `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx` |
| Types/interfaces | PascalCase — `interface Product` |
| Constants | SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE |

---

## Folder Rules

| Code type | Location |
|---|---|
| Route pages/layouts | `app/` only |
| UI components | `components/` |
| Utilities, API clients | `lib/` |
| React hooks | `hooks/` |
| React context providers | `context/` |
| i18n message files | `messages/` |
| i18n config | `i18n/` |
| Shared types | `packages/types/` (not inside apps) |
| Shared UI primitives | `packages/ui/` (not inside apps) |

**Never:**
- Put business logic in `components/`
- Put React/JSX in `lib/`
- Put types in `components/` or `app/`
- Call APIs directly from components — always through `lib/` clients

---

## Styling Rules

- Tailwind utility classes only — no inline styles
- Use `cn()` from `lib/cn.ts` for conditional classes
- Use logical CSS properties for RTL compatibility: `ms-*`, `me-*`, `ps-*`, `pe-*`, `start`, `end`
- No `left`/`right` positioning on elements that need RTL support

---

## Prohibited Actions

- Do NOT modify: `ARCHITECTURE.md`, `DEVELOPMENT_RULES.md`, `DECISIONS.md`, `TASKS.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `ROADMAP.md`, `SESSION_GUIDE.md`, `PROJECT_BRIEF.md`, `PROJECT_OPERATIONS.md`, `DEPLOYMENT.md`, `docs/cursor-workflow.md`, `docs/notion/*`
- Do NOT commit `.env` files
- Do NOT use `console.log` — use structured logging where logging is needed
- Do NOT add `eslint-disable` without a comment explaining why
- Do NOT add dependencies without them being in the task brief
- Do NOT fix bugs or refactor code outside the task scope ("while I'm here" changes are forbidden)

---

## Before Reporting Done

Checklist — ALL must pass:

- [ ] Every file in the brief's "Scope" section has been addressed
- [ ] No files outside the "Scope" were modified
- [ ] `npx tsc --noEmit` — zero errors
- [ ] `npx next build` — zero errors (in the relevant app)
- [ ] All acceptance criteria in the brief are met
- [ ] No `any` types introduced without justification
- [ ] No hardcoded strings that should be i18n keys
